{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> δῆλος</b> <br /> (also <i>Doric dialect</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Archytas Tarentinus Philosophus 1, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 11.79, etc., and _Aeolic dialect_, compare πρόδηλος)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], η, ον, also ος, ον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 1197 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>Epic dialect</i> <b>δέελος</b>: <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> properly <b>visible, conspicuous,</b> δέελον δ᾽ ἐπὶ σῆμά τ᾽ ἔθηκε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.466, but: \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> commonly, <b>clear</b> to the mind, <b>manifest,</b> νῦν δ᾽ ἤδη τόδε δ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 20.333, etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> δ. εἰμι is frequently used with <i>participle</i>, δ. ἐστιν ἀλγεινῶς φέρων i.e. <b>it is clear</b> that he takes it ill, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1011, compare “OT” 673, 1008, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οἳ ἂν δ. ὦσι μὴ ἐπιτρέψοντες who are <b>clearly</b> not going to permit, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.71; with ὡς, δ. ἐστιν ὥς τι δρασείων κακόν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 326; δ. ἔσεσθε ὡς ὀργιζόμενοι 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 12.90, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.5.9 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δ. ὁρᾶσθαι.. ὤν being as was <b>plainly</b> to be seen, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 350: with ὅτι\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] and a Verb, δ. ἐστιν ὅτι.. ἀκήκοεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 333; δ. ἡ οἰκοδομία ὅτι κατὰ σπουδὴν ἐγένετο 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.9; δ. ἔσται ὅτι.. 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 12.50: sometimes the \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>participle</i> or <i>relative</i> clause must be supplied, καταγελᾷς μου, δ. εἶ (i.e. καταγελῶν) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1407, compare [prev. author] “Lys.” 919 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δῆλοι δέ (i.e. οὐ μένοντες) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.10. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> δῆλον ποιεῖν <b>show plainly,</b> τινὶ ὅτι.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 6.34, etc.\">Refs</a>]: with <i>participle</i>, δῆλον ἐποιήσατε.. μηδίσαντες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 3.64. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> δῆλον (i.e. ἐστί) <b>it is manifest,</b> αὐτὸς πρὸς αὑτοῦ· δῆλον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 906; ἀλγεινά, Πρόκνη, δῆλον [prev. author] “fragment” 585; ἐκ πίθω ἀντλεῖς, δῆλον 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 10.13 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δῆλον δέ, to introduce a proof, followed by γάρ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.11, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Coloribus” 799a5, etc.; δῆλον γάρ 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 63; δῆλον ὅτι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.38, etc.; τὰ Κύρου δῆλον ὅτι οὕτως ἔχει 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.3.9, compare “Cyr.” 2.4.24, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], see at {δηλονότι}: in <i>plural</i>, δῆλα δή, δ. δ. καὶ ταῦτα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Crito” 48b; ἢ δ. δ. ὅτι..; [prev. author] “Prt.” 309a, etc.: hence as \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <i>adverb</i>, usually written δηλαδή (which see). <br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> <i>adverb</i> δήλως is rejected by <i>Attic dialect</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 6.207. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> δῆλοι, οἱ, <b>Urim,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.1Ki.28.6, +others (Cf. δέατο.) \">LXX</a>]","strongNumber":"G1212","accentedUnicode":"δῆλος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1212","matchingForm":"δῆλος","stepTransliteration":"dēlos","gloss":"Urim","_zh_tw_Gloss":"明顯, 露出來了","_es_Gloss":"claro ","_zh_Gloss":"明显, 露出来了"},{"strongNumber":"H0224","matchingForm":"אוּרִים","stepTransliteration":"u.rim","gloss":"Urim","_zh_tw_Gloss":"烏陵","_es_Gloss":"Urim","_zh_Gloss":"乌陵"}],"shortDef":"clear, plain, evident","mediumDef":" <BR> § clear, plain, evident <br /><i>primarily</i> <b>clearly visible; plain, manifest, evident,</b> <ref='Mat.26.73'>Mt. 26:73</ref>; <ref='1Co.15.27'>1Cor. 15:27;</ref> <ref='Gal.3.11'>Gal. 3:11</ref>*","stepGloss":"Urim","stepTransliteration":"dēlos","count":4,"_es_Definition":"claro, evidente ","_zh_tw_Definition":"清楚的, 明顯的, 顯露的","_zh_Definition":"清楚的, 明显的, 显露的","_step_Type":"word","_stepDetailLexicalTag":"[[\"named\",\"H0224\",\"Urim\",7,\"אוּרִים\"],[\"in Greek\",\"G1212\",\"Urim\",4,\"δῆλος\"]]","_vi_Definition":"rõ ràng","_zh_tw_Gloss":"明顯, 露出來了","_es_Gloss":"claro ","_zh_Gloss":"明显, 露出来了"}]}